    <text id="R14696266T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union General Phil Sheridan reports to General George Crook in January, 1865. He
                    discusses the return of scouts from Staunton bearing news of a possible
                    Confederate raid.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    HDQRS. MIDDLE MILITARY DIVISION,
                    <name type="recipient">Maj.-Gen. CROOK,<lb/> Cmdg. Department of West Virginia,
                        Cumberland, Md.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-01-25">January 25, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Two of my scouts have just returned from Staunton. They think that Rosser
                    meditates a raid westward to Weston or Clarksburg as soon as the weather
                    moderates. Keep a sharp lookout for him at Bull's Gap and Buckhannon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>P. H. SHERIDAN,<lb/> Maj.-Gen., Cmdg.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
